Gemini 2.5 Pro API Documentation
Chat completion using Google's Gemini 2.5 Pro model via OpenAI-compatible API

Overview
This document describes how to use the Gemini 2.5 Pro model for chat completion with multimodal capabilities (text, images, video, audio, PDF) and advanced features like function calling, Google Search grounding, structured output, and reasoning.

Authentication
All API requests require a Bearer Token in the request header:

text
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY
Get API Key:

Visit API Key Management Page to get your API Key

Add to request header: Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY

API Information
URL: POST https://api.kie.ai/gemini-2.5-pro/v1/chat/completions

Content-Type: application/json

Request Parameters
Required Parameters
Parameter	Type	Description
messages	array	Array of message objects (see below)
Optional Parameters
Parameter	Type	Description
stream	boolean	If true, returns responses as server-sent events (SSE) with incremental deltas
tools	array	Defines functions the model can call (e.g., googleSearch)
response_format	object	JSON Schema object defining the response structure (mutually exclusive with tools)
include_thoughts	boolean	Whether to include reasoning tokens in the response
reasoning_effort	string	Effort level for reasoning: "low", "medium", "high"
Messages Structure
The messages array contains conversation history. Each message has:

Field	Type	Description
role	string	"user", "assistant", or "system"
content	array	Array of content parts (text and/or media)
Content Part Types
Text Part
json
{
  "type": "text",
  "text": "Your text prompt here"
}
Media Part (Unified Structure)
For images, video, audio, and PDF files, use the same structure:

json
{
  "type": "image_url",
  "image_url": {
    "url": "https://your-file-url.com/file.mp4"
  }
}
Important:

The type field is fixed as "image_url" for all file types

The image_url key name remains unchanged

Only the url value changes to point to your specific media file

Tools Parameter
The tools parameter allows the model to call external functions.

Google Search Tool
Enable grounding with Google Search (mutually exclusive with response_format):

json
{
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "googleSearch"
      }
    }
  ]
}
Restriction: Google Search and function calling cannot be used together with response_format.

Response Format Parameter
The response_format parameter defines the structure of the response. When provided, the model generates responses conforming to the JSON Schema.

json
{
  "response_format": {
    "type": "json_schema",
    "json_schema": {
      "name": "structured_output",
      "strict": true,
      "schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "response": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
Important: response_format and tools are mutually exclusive.

Streaming Support
When stream: true is set, the API returns responses as server-sent events (SSE) with Content-Type: text/event-stream. Each event contains partial message content, enabling real-time display of responses.

Request Example
bash
curl --location --request POST 'https://api.kie.ai/gemini-2.5-pro/v1/chat/completions' \
--header 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data-raw '{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "What is in this image?"
        },
        {
          "type": "image_url",
          "image_url": {
            "url": "https://example.com/image.png"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "googleSearch"
      }
    }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "include_thoughts": true,
  "reasoning_effort": "high",
  "response_format": {
    "type": "json_schema",
    "json_schema": {
      "name": "structured_output",
      "strict": true,
      "schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "response": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}'
Response Example
Non-streaming Response
json
{
  "id": "chatcmpl-example-123",
  "object": "chat.completion",
  "created": 1677652288,
  "model": "gemini-2.5-pro",
  "choices": [
    {
      "index": 0,
      "message": {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "The image shows a scenic mountain landscape with pine trees and a lake."
      },
      "finish_reason": "stop"
    }
  ],
  "usage": {
    "prompt_tokens": 10,
    "completion_tokens": 50,
    "total_tokens": 60
  }
}
Streaming Response
When stream: true, responses are sent as SSE events with data: lines containing JSON fragments.

Response Parameters
Parameter	Type	Description
id	string	Unique identifier for the completion
object	string	Always "chat.completion"
created	integer	Unix timestamp of creation
model	string	Model name ("gemini-2.5-pro")
choices	array	Array of completion choices
choices[].index	integer	Index of the choice
choices[].message	object	Message object (non-streaming)
choices[].message.role	string	"assistant"
choices[].message.content	string	Generated content
choices[].finish_reason	string	"stop", "length", "tool_calls", etc.
usage	object	Token usage statistics
usage.prompt_tokens	integer	Tokens in the prompt
usage.completion_tokens	integer	Tokens in the completion
usage.total_tokens	integer	Total tokens used
Error Codes
Status Code	Description
200	Request successful
400	Invalid request parameters
401	Authentication failed, please check API Key
429	Request rate limit exceeded
500	Internal server error
